  "text": "HomeEditors' PicksThe two indie brands collaborated on a delightful pearl-adorned silk scrunchie and a beaded statement necklace.The Crown Affair x Éliou Venus Scrunchie, $88, available here and Dianna Necklace, $240, available here.Photos: Courtesy of Crown AffairEditors' Picks are the Fashionista team's true (#notspon) fashion and beauty obsessions, handpicked by professionals who see it all.Spring seems to finally be spring-ing, and I'm turning my attention to my warm-weather wardrobe. I typically focus on the basics: a versatile, lightweight dress; a good pair of jorts; some cute, comfortable sandals. But a few joyful, perfectly summery accessories have also caught my eye recently. Hair-care brand Crown Affair partnered with jewelry and clothing label Éliou to create what I'm going to prematurely deem the must-have accessories of summer 2025.The collab includes Crown Affair's signature green silk scrunchie, leveled up with a collection of natural freshwater pearl pendants, and a green satin-corded beaded statement necklace. Both of them can be worn multiple ways, ideally beachside, all summer long.I was already a huge fan of Crown Affair's skinny silk scrunchies (The Scrunchie No. 001), which work perfectly on my fine hair and are super gentle on strands. (I also love sleeping in them for minimal bedhead.) But a version adorned with pearls that can be worn as both a hair accessory and a bracelet? Sign. Me. Up.Scroll to ContinueRecommended ArticlesThe necklace, meanwhile, looks like a chic, adult version of jewelry you'd buy on vacation as a tween. Per the brand, the colored beads are \"a reflection of sun-drenched days and the effortless beauty of nature,\" but I also find them reminiscent of a candy necklace. Because it's adjustable, the piece can be worn as a proper necklace, a tightened choker, a bracelet or an anklet (just wrap it around twice). Crown Affair even suggests fashioning it into a bag charm (very 2025) or hat accessory, offering up styling inspo on its Instagram.This isn't Crown Affair's first covetable collab: The brand previously partnered with fellow indie beauty brand Nette on a mint-green candle. I'm guessing it also won't be the brand's last. The Crown Affair x Éliou Venus Scrunchie, $88, available here and Dianna Necklace, $240, available here.Please note: These products were gifted. Occasionally, we use affiliate links on our site. In no way do either affect our editorial decision-making.Tune into the Fashionista Network to join the conversation with fashion and beauty industry leaders. Sign up here.Subscribe to Our Newsletter",
