ce.jpg\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" width=\"1200\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/phoenix-picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eI was already a huge fan of Crown Affair\u0026#39;s skinny silk scrunchies (\u003ca href=\"https://go.shopmy.us/p-16367998\" rel=\"noopener\" onclick=\"return phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eThe Scrunchie No. 001\u003c/a\u003e), which work perfectly on my fine hair and are super gentle on strands. (I also love sleeping in them for minimal bedhead.) But a version adorned with pearls that can be worn as both a hair accessory and a bracelet? Sign. Me. Up.\u003c/p\u003e\u003csection id=\"phx-3\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eScroll to Continue\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"phx-5\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 role=\"heading\" aria-level=\"2\"\u003eRecommended Articles\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/section\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe necklace, meanwhile, looks like a chic, adult version of jewelry you\u0026#39;d buy on vacation as a tween. Per the brand, the colored beads are \u0026#34;a reflection of sun-drenched days and the effortless beauty of nature,\u0026#34; but I also find them reminiscent of a candy necklace. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eBecause it\u0026#39;s adjustable, the piece can be worn as a proper necklace, a tightened choker, a bracelet or an anklet (just wrap it around twice). Crown Affair even suggests fashioning it into a bag charm (very 2025) or hat accessory, offering up \u003ca href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/DIbtpkDJOaG/?img_index=1\" rel=\"noopener\" onclick=\"return phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" target=\"_blank\"\u003estyling inspo on its Instagram\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis isn\u0026#39;t Crown Affair\u0026#39;s first covetable collab: The brand \u003ca href=\"https://fashionista.com/2024/10/nette-crown-affair-take-your-time-candle-review\"\u003epreviously partnered with fellow indie beauty brand Nette\u003c/a\u003e on a mint-green \u003ca href=\"https://fashionista.com/tag/candles\"\u003ecandle\u003c/a\u003e. I\u0026#39;m guessing it also won\u0026#39;t be the brand\u0026#39;s last. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Crown Affair x Éliou Venus Scrunchie, $88, available \u003ca href=\"https://go.shopmy.us/p-16342571\" rel=\"noopener\" onclick=\"return phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ehere\u003c/a\u003e and Dianna Necklace, $240, available \u003ca href=\"https://go.shopmy.us/p-16342602\" rel=\"noopener\" onclick=\"return phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ehere\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eP\u003c/em\u003e\u003cem\u003elease note: These products were gifted. Occasionally, we use affiliate links on our site. In no way do either affect our editorial decision-making.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://f.chat/S522\" rel=\"noopener\" onclick=\"return phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eTune into the Fashionista Network to join the conversation with fashion and beauty industry leaders. Sign up here.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/article\u003e\u003c/section\u003e\u003csection id=\"phxbrandengagement-2\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"phx-7\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 role=\"heading\" aria-level=\"2\"\u003eSubscribe to Our Newsletter\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cphoenix-picture\u003e\u003c/phoenix-picture\u003e\u003c/section\u003e\u003csection id=\"phxlisthub-3\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"phx-8\"\u003e\u003ch2 role=\"heading\" aria-level=\"2\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://fashionista.com/.image/cs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good/MTQ1NTQ5OTY2NzI5ODE1NjA3/mtqwndi3ntcznze1oda1njgw-1.svg\" alt=\"Related Stories\"/\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cphoenix-hub data-group-size=\"4\" data-first-group-size=\"3\"